      <h1>Title — Official Copy summary</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        The parsed Official Copy summary as HMLR returns it: number &amp;
        extents, metadata, proprietorship &amp; lease, charges, restrictions,
        notices, cautions. The OC summary is the legal anchor for every
        ownership claim and every encumbrance over the title; this cluster
        breaks it into seven sub-pages so each conceptual region of the
        register reads on its own.
      </p>
      <h2 id="subpages">Pages in this cluster</h2>
      <ul class="cluster-index">
        <li><a href="38b1-title-number.html"><strong>Title · number &amp; extents</strong></a> — HMLR title number and the title-extents geometry.</li>
        <li><a href="38b2-title-oc-meta.html"><strong>OC summary · metadata &amp; property</strong></a> — official copy date/time, edition, price-paid entry, property address, register-entry indicators.</li>
        <li><a href="38b3-title-oc-owners.html"><strong>OC summary · proprietorship &amp; lease</strong></a> — proprietorship register entries and any lease referenced from the summary.</li>
        <li><a href="38b4-title-oc-charges-main.html"><strong>OC summary · charges (main)</strong></a> — charges, noted charges, equitable charges.</li>
        <li><a href="38b5-title-oc-charges-other.html"><strong>OC summary · other charges &amp; restrictions</strong></a> — discount charges, rent charges, vendor's lien, restriction details.</li>
        <li><a href="38b6-title-oc-notices-main.html"><strong>OC summary · notices</strong></a> — agreed notices, unilateral notices, creditors' notices, document detail.</li>
        <li><a href="38b7-title-oc-notices-other.html"><strong>OC summary · cautions, bankruptcy, rights</strong></a> — bankruptcy, cautions, deed of postponement, green-out, home rights, right of pre-emption, etc.</li>
      </ul>
